course_title: Differential Calculus with Applications to Physical Sciences and Engineering

sections.comments: MATH 100 is comprised of a two hour asynchronous lecture and a one hour synchronous workshop. Attending lectures will not be required as they will be recorded and can be viewed at any time, but attending workshops will be required. All students are to register in MATH 100 101 and a workshop. Some workshops are reserved for STT students, but there are many workshops with general seats. Workshops later in the evening have been scheduled for students in different time zones, please be considerate when you register. If you cannot register in one of the available workshops, we will place you later in the summer.Prerequisites for this course will be strictly enforced.  If you have 80% or higher in Pre-Calculus 12 but do nothave the high school calculus prerequisite for this course, please register yourself in MATH 180.  If you do not have a grade of 80% or better in Pre-Calclulus 12, please register in MATH 110.
